text.paragraph:
Continuous long-term use of pimecrolimus cream, 1% should be avoided, and application should be limited to areas of involvement with atopic dermatitis [see 

                        Warnings and Precautions (5.1)
                     ].

The use of pimecrolimus cream, 1% may cause local symptoms such as skin burning (burning sensation, stinging, soreness) or pruritus. Localized symptoms are most common during the first few days of pimecrolimus cream, 1% application and typically improve as the lesions of atopic dermatitis resolve [see 

                              Adverse Reactions (6.1)
                           ].
